name: Qasim Rafique
bio:
• Scottish
• Based in USA 
• Relationship/Life Coach 
• Published Author
• Infidelity Recovery Coach
• Public Speaker
• @matw_project Ambassador

social_posts.post_text:
As a relationship coach my focus is to understands human needs and desires within the context of the way we feel, interact, connect and behave with ourselves and others. 

I offer an online space in which difficult feelings can be explored between couples or individuals without judgment or blame. 

I deal with issues including, but not limited to: 

Stress
Depression
Anxiety
Interpersonal Issues
Premarital coaching
Sexual and Emotional Disconnect
Infidelity 
Divorce 
Parenting
Fighting and Defensiveness
Communication
Codependency
Addiction 
Islamic Identity
Narcissism...and more

My role is to provide a safe and informed place in which individuals or couples can become clear about what is happening between them, allowing them to make healthy choices, and move forward to make decisions with greater clarity and understanding.

I provide relationship, marital and life coaching from an Islamic perspective using Cognitive Behavioural Therapy & Neuro-Linguistic Programming techniques. I help couples more truthfully know themselves and each other. This leads to a better understanding of how their inner selves are affecting their day-to-day lives.

For more information or booking enquires check out my website (link) via my IG profile. 

Qasim Rafique 
Relationship Coach
www.QasimRafique.com

How To Improve Your Relationship Part 3 

As a relationship coach, I help individuals and couples understand their needs and desires within the context of their interactions with themselves and others. My goal is to provide a safe space where difficult feelings can be explored without judgment or blame.I specialize in helping people deal with issues such as stress, depression, anxiety, interpersonal issues, premarital coaching, sexual and emotional disconnect, infidelity, divorce, parenting, fighting and defensiveness, communication, codependency, addiction, Islamic identity, narcissism and more.My role is to provide a safe and informed place in which individuals or couples can become clear about what is happening between them. This allows them to make healthy choices and move forward with greater clarity and understanding.I offer relationship, marital and life coaching from an Islamic perspective using Cognitive Behavioural Therapy & Neuro-Linguistic Programming techniques. This leads to a better understanding of how their inner selves are affecting their day-to-day lives.For more information or booking inquiries please check out my website (link) via my IG profile.

As a relationship coach, my mission is to help individuals and couples understand their needs and desires within the context of their interactions with themselves and others. I provide a safe space for exploration without judgment or blame, and offer a wide range of services to help people deal with issues such as stress, depression, anxiety, interpersonal conflicts, and more.

My approach is grounded in Islamic values, and I use Cognitive Behavioural Therapy and Neuro-Linguistic Programming techniques to provide tailored coaching to each client. My goal is to help clients gain clarity and understanding, make healthy choices, and move forward with confidence and purpose.

If you're looking to strengthen your relationship, overcome challenges, or simply gain a deeper understanding of yourself and your partner, I invite you to visit my website and book an appointment today. Let's work together to achieve the happy and fulfilling life you deserve.

Stepping into Madina is a powerful immersion into the essence of Islam. The air carries the whispers of centuries, the hallowed grounds resonate with a spiritual energy, and the sight of the Prophet's Mosque evokes a profound sense of awe and humility. It always feels like coming home when in the beloved city of our Prophet, peace be upon him. It's a soul-stirring return, where the past converges with the present in a potent embrace of faith and history.

As a relationship coach, my mission is to help individuals and couples understand their needs and desires within the context of their interactions with themselves and others. I provide a safe space for exploration without judgment or blame, and offer a wide range of services to help people deal with issues such as stress, depression, anxiety, interpersonal conflicts, and more.

My approach is grounded in Islamic values, and I use Cognitive Behavioural Therapy and Neuro-Linguistic Programming techniques to provide tailored coaching to each client. My goal is to help clients gain clarity and understanding, make healthy choices, and move forward with confidence and purpose.

If you're looking to strengthen your relationship, overcome challenges, or simply gain a deeper understanding of yourself and your partner, I invite you to visit my website and book an appointment today. Let's work together to achieve the happy and fulfilling life you deserve.
